content:
A dashboard isn't just for reading. It's for carrying on a conversation based on one or more datasets that matter to your company. Don't only look at the picturesâ€”use the tools on the dashboard to dive deeper into the data that you care about.

You read a Salesforce CRM Analytics dashboard interactively by clicking its displayed elements. Every element is a picture of a live, filtered query.

Selection-Based Filters

A selection-based filter lets you apply whatever filters you wish while viewing the dashboard. For example, set the minimum and maximum values in a range widget to make the dashboard show the amounts that fall within that range.

Key Performance Indicators

Some information is best measured by a single number, also known as key performance indicators. Some number elements can be filtered based on selections in charts and filters.

Charts

A rich variety of charts shows you data from multiple angles. Many parts of a chart are interactive. For example, click a bar in a bar chart and watch what happens.

Tables

A table provides the record-level details. You can sort tables to show the top and bottom records. You can also create calculated columns in tables to compute values based on existing data.
title: Understanding Key Elements of a CRM Analytics Dashboard
